description.p:
The Question Version feature is implemented in the form of a Question Version Index and two separate functions Set QVI and Select Question. In FIGS. 19a and 19b, these elements are shown as follows:





Global Version Index (QVI) is data item 1020;

Set QVI is process 1000;

Select Question process is shown as process 1001.

claim.claim-text:
46. A computerized method for generating a critical curve to assess a patient's need for medical treatment, comprising:
determining disease specific health parameters from the patient's medical history;
adding current health parameters, corresponding to a particular patient having been diagnosed with a particular disease, to the patient's medical history;
plotting a patient specific curve consisting of health parameters measured against time;
performing statistical analysis on the patient specific critical curve;
accessing a standard critical curve for the disease;
comparing values from the patient specific critical curve to the standard critical curve to determine if a threshold has been met; and
indicating medical treatment if the value threshold has been met.

48. A computerized system for generating a critical curve to assess a patient's need for medical treatment, the system comprising:
means for determining disease specific health parameters from the patient's medical history;
means for adding current health parameters, corresponding to a particular patient having been diagnosed with a particular disease, to the patient's medical history;
means for plotting a patient specific curve consisting of health parameters measured against time;
means for performing statistical analysis on the patient specific critical curve;
means for accessing a standard critical curve for the disease;
means for comparing values from the patient specific critical curve to the standard critical curve to determine if a threshold has been met; and
means for indicating medical treatment if the value threshold has been met.
